The production of a SARS-CoV-2 vaccine has met major obstacles since the beginning such as the absence of clear data on the immune response elicited by SARS-CoV-2 and the notable side effects observed in SARS-CoV and MERS vaccine candidates (
 Bolles et al., 2011; 
 Tseng et al., 2012; 
 Agrawal et al., 2016). Additionally, a decreasing confidence of the general population in the vaccination effort can become a major obstacle for the development of a efficient vaccination programme.
